subpage: chronic-disease
parent: problem.auckland.health.system_access
order: 2
updated: "2026-04-26"
summary: >
  Chronic disease (diabetes, cardiovascular disease, respiratory disease)
  is concentrated in high-deprivation Auckland communities; Pacific
  Aucklanders have diabetes rates approximately three times the national
  average. Late diagnosis due to primary care access barriers generates
  higher-acuity presentations and worse outcomes. The food environment,
  housing quality, and urban form are upstream structural drivers that
  clinical care alone cannot address.
